-- Loewe Says It’s Had No Contact With Apple, Handelsblatt Reports
-- B y   S h e e n a g h   M a t t h e w s
-- 2012-05-16T06:29:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-16/loewe-says-it-s-had-no-contact-with-apple-handelsblatt-reports.html
Loewe AG (LOE) , a German television maker,
has had “no contact” with  Apple Inc. (AAPL)  about being taken over,
Chief Executive Officer Oliver Seidl said yesterday at the
company’s annual meeting,  Handelsblatt reported .  Supervisory board chairman Rainer Hecker, who is also a
shareholder, said he doesn’t know of any takeover intentions,
the newspaper said.  Loewe shares climbed as much as 10 percent yesterday after
 AppleInsider  reported that Apple offered to purchase the
Kronach-based company for 87.3 million euros ($111 million). The
stock closed down 0.2 percent at 5.99 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sheenagh Matthews in Frankfurt at 
